                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.55/22.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-09-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 17, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Government of Panama has today revoked exequatur of Ow Yang King, Chinese
                    Consul General, on the ground of encouraging Chinese not to comply with Law 50
                    and thus becoming persona non grata <pb facs="1224" n="1120" xml:id="pg_1120"/>
                    to the Government. Period of registration expired September 15 without the
                    Chinese having complied with the law but also without coercive measures as yet
                    on the part of the Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wicker</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
